\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0
\par\plain {\f1\fs24\b1\i0 Before Eorzea}
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Baatarsaikhan Kha was born in 1554-6A on the Azim Steppe; she was raised until the age of 4 on the Steppe in a small offshoot of the Kha tribe, who unlike most Steppe-dwellers lived on the fringes of Xaela territory and actively sought out elements of non-Auri culture. Thus, Baatar learned to speak not only Xaela, but also Eorzean - and, if she had remained on the Steppe and followed her parents\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92 wishes, would have learned Yamago as well.}
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Due to the threat of both Garlean incursion and other, more hostile tribes, part of the Kha tribe elected to flee the Steppe; thanks to their contacts with off-continent traders, this offshoot was able to make a deal with the crew of the }{\f2\fs24\b0\i1 Little Kweh}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 , and arraigned to be given passage to Eorzea. Leading up to the day of pickup (7-2U-6A), Garlean troop movement and hostile tribes forced the refugees to move closer to the city; Garlean regulars captured several of the clan\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s scouts and forced them to make a run for the ships in the early morning of the 8th. In the rush through the captured port, a good portion of the clan was killed; of the 79 people who intended to make the journey to Eorzea only 28 actually made it to the boats. Chinjaal and Gonbaatar both died holding back the Garlean troops.}
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Baatar spent the next two months aboard the }{\f2\fs24\b0\i1 Little Kweh}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 ; though she and the other refugees were kept belowdecks whenever the ship was in port she was still able to receive gifts from each port, as well as instruction in Eorzean Common, numbers and figures. She also was instructed in the basics of Steppe-living (survival tactics, cooking, and the basics of axe, sword, spear and bow.) She took to the axe quickly, and would strike up a friendship with many of the crew - including Pfarberk Iyrnfhissyn and Arnar Young. }
